Location: Ria de Aveiro--frente ribeirinha de São Jacinto
Observation Details: Large goose, greyish forewing, dark head and neck, heavy looking bill, bright orange yellow feet. Seen earlier flying directly towards me then overhead and thought to be a greylag because of greyish forewing and heavy bill (seen against sky). Now seen flying back upriver in excellent light. No sign of any plumage variation which would suggest a domestic origin. Feet were bright and more yellowish than orange. Clearly a bizarre record.
